00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:19,778
                    Oh! Stop!

261
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:21,613
      Yak eating new Eating Hut!

262
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:28,353
    Psst, Prince Rutherford,
       what are we doing?

263
00:11:28,755 --> 00:11:29,721
                 It's obvious.

264
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:31,423
       This New Music Hut!

265
00:11:31,725 --> 00:11:34,525
Oh. So we're swaying to... ?

266
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:37,428
                   Ssshhh. Pink Pony ruin snow
                    music with talking.

267
00:11:38,975 --> 00:11:41,275
               ♪♪

268
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,135
                        [rumble]

269
00:11:44,237 --> 00:11:45,403
What was yak?

270
00:11:45,605 --> 00:11:47,238
            Yak stomach rumbles.

271
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,606
                     Yak hungry.

272
00:11:48,808 --> 00:11:49,440
     Sshh.

273
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,276
Prince Yak will
hear yak!

274
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:54,045
               But snow worse
             than yak ever seen!

275
00:11:54,347 --> 00:11:55,413
Yak know.

276
00:11:55,515 --> 00:11:57,015
Yak hungry too.

277
00:11:57,617 --> 00:11:59,484
    [gasp!] Gummy, did you hear that?

278
00:11:59,586 --> 00:12:01,119
    They can't make it work.

279
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:04,589
       Yaks stop swaying.

280
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:05,757
           Music over.

281
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:08,326
      If Twilight and the others
        knew what was going on,

282
00:12:08,428 --> 00:12:10,495
      they would be here to help
        in a pony's heartbeat.

283
00:12:10,797 --> 00:12:12,296
              I have to convince
               Prince Rutherford

284
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:14,365
     that asking for help is OK.

285
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,566
        Will you help me, Gummy?

286
00:12:16,868 --> 00:12:17,567
           Thank you!

287
00:12:17,669 --> 00:12:20,271
     And see, asking you to
    help wasn't hard at all!

288
00:12:21,184 --> 00:12:21,784
[slurp]

289
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:25,510
          Pink Pony has
       gathered you around

290
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:28,146
       the New Ceremonial
         Yak Firepit...

291
00:12:28,948 --> 00:12:30,381
    ... to tell you a story.

292
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,183
     A yak tradition, right?

293
00:12:32,285 --> 00:12:34,185
           [agreement]

294
00:12:34,287 --> 00:12:35,186
              Yay!

295
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,823
         This is a story
       about a group of...

296
00:12:38,525 --> 00:12:41,693
         er.. goats, who live
          in the desert.

297
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:44,795
      There was a sandstorm
    and their entire village

298
00:12:44,897 --> 00:12:46,597
       was buried in sand.

299
00:12:46,899 --> 00:12:48,500
There was nothing they could do.

300
00:12:48,802 --> 00:12:53,171
They knew they could not survive
   on only eating sand-wiches!

301
00:12:54,073 --> 00:12:54,573
             Get it?

302
00:12:57,075 --> 00:12:57,776
               OK.

303
00:12:57,878 --> 00:13:01,980
   Anyway, finally, the goat's
       brave, wise leader

304
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:06,451
        --let's just call
    him Prince er.. Drutherford-- heh, heh

305
00:13:06,553 --> 00:13:09,087
   decides that they couldn't
      do it by themselves.

306
00:13:09,189 --> 00:13:12,423
   So he asked the neighboring
     town of uh, Bovineville

307
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:15,226
 to come help them. Yeah! Cows!

308
00:13:15,328 --> 00:13:16,526
        The magical cows
        helped the goats.

309
00:13:16,628 --> 00:13:18,530
      Everyone survived and
    lived happily ever after.

310
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:22,401
  Because they asked for help.

311
00:13:23,203 --> 00:13:23,668
            The end!

312
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:26,971
           [shouting]

313
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:29,240
         So what is the
      moral of that story?

314
00:13:29,442 --> 00:13:32,043
       Is it A: asking for
           help is OK?

315
00:13:32,445 --> 00:13:35,313
       B: asking for help
         saves the day?

316
00:13:35,615 --> 00:13:39,484
      Or C: asking for help
     is good for everypony!?

317
00:13:39,686 --> 00:13:41,619
D: goats weak
and horrible!

318
00:13:41,721 --> 00:13:44,556
Magic Bovines need to stay
out of goats' business!

319
00:13:45,558 --> 00:13:47,826
                Um... not quite.

320
00:13:48,228 --> 00:13:50,695
             Any-yak wanna shout
             out another answer?

321
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:53,364
                [whistling wind]

322
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,800
             [groan]

323
00:13:56,745 --> 00:13:58,245
[scrape] [scrape]

324
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:00,169
                 Pinkie: Hey,
              Prince Rutherford.

325
00:14:00,271 --> 00:14:03,708
   I want to talk to you about
something -- what are you doing?

326
00:14:03,810 --> 00:14:07,512
Eh.. Yak snow bed got a
little melty last night.

327
00:14:08,214 --> 00:14:09,447
                OK, yeah.

328
00:14:09,549 --> 00:14:11,282
       That's what I want
      to talk to you about.

329
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:14,919
You know, these yak snow
beds are the fluffiest

330
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:15,954
I've ever slept in!

331
00:14:16,056 --> 00:14:17,054
They're so comfortable,

332
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,157
you forget that it's just
a cold block of ice.

333
00:14:19,259 --> 00:14:21,960
And the yak snow
sandwiches, mmm, mmm!

334
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:23,995
I hate it when food
burns your mouth

335
00:14:24,097 --> 00:14:25,497
or overwhelms
it with flavor.

336
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:28,366
         Oh! Yak hates that too!

337
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:31,035
You know who would
really, really enjoy

338
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:32,237
these snow sandwiches?

339
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:34,806
Twilight Sparkle and
the other ponies!

340
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:38,276
Oh! Hey, I have an idea!

341
00:14:38,778 --> 00:14:41,279
   Why don't I go to Ponyville
    and bring them back here?

342
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:43,848
   Ponies like snow sandwich?

343
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:46,517
Oh! Ponies love snow
   sandwiches!

344
00:14:46,619 --> 00:14:48,086
And, hey, while they're here,

345
00:14:48,188 --> 00:14:49,954
you can ask if they'll
clear the snow away.

346
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:51,090
Fun, right?

347
00:14:52,292 --> 00:14:54,325
   When Prince was little yak,

348
00:14:54,527 --> 00:14:56,828
        Prince stomped on
        ground too hard.

349
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:59,664
       Made deep hole and
         fell into hole.

350
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:01,866
      Ice froze over hole.

351
00:15:02,168 --> 00:15:06,237
   Prince waved to friends and
 family from inside frozen hole.

352
00:15:06,439 --> 00:15:08,106
     Waited for spring thaw.

353
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:10,741
     Prince survived on own.

354
00:15:11,043 --> 00:15:12,143
Wait a minute..

355
00:15:12,345 --> 00:15:14,679
You spent the whole
 winter in a hole?

356
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:17,482
       Yes. And yak never
          ask for help!

357
00:15:17,706 --> 00:15:18,206
[horn bump]

358
00:15:19,485 --> 00:15:22,953
  OK, first of all, how did you
      make such a deep hole

359
00:15:23,055 --> 00:15:23,688
         from stomping?

360
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,590
         And how did it
      freeze over so fast?

361
00:15:25,892 --> 00:15:27,492
      And how could you see
     your family and friends

362
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:29,260
      to wave to them from
      inside a frozen hole?

363
00:15:29,362 --> 00:15:32,496
 Even if all that was possible,
  how did you breathe in there!?

364
00:15:33,665 --> 00:15:35,733
        YAKS DON'T ASK FOR HELP!

365
00:15:37,002 --> 00:15:38,669
    But the yaks are hungry!

366
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:40,638
       And who knows when
       the snow will melt?

367
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,438
          I just don't
        understand why--

368
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:47,412
 Ah yes, is clear now that Pink
 Pony does not understand Yaks!

369
00:15:47,714 --> 00:15:50,381
 Honorary Yak status rescinded!

370
00:15:52,417 --> 00:15:54,318
            Bang! Pretend there
                 is door!

371
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:56,620
              I just slammed it!

372
00:15:57,689 --> 00:15:59,390
Fine, be stubborn!

373
00:15:59,514 --> 00:16:01,914
               ♪♪

374
00:16:05,598 --> 00:16:07,999
   Oooh! Those yaks are so stubborn!

375
00:16:08,101 --> 00:16:10,501
   They refuse to ask for help
    even though they need it.

376
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:12,503
       Well, this Official
      Friendship Ambassador

377
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:14,905
    is going to take matters
      into her own hooves.

378
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:16,240
         I'll show them.

379
00:16:18,977 --> 00:16:20,144
You're right, Gummy.

380
00:16:20,246 --> 00:16:21,444
I am too worked up.

381
00:16:21,546 --> 00:16:24,182
A road trip game would
officially calm me down.

382
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:25,682
    I know!

383
00:16:25,784 --> 00:16:27,952
Let's play "Twenty
Million Questions."

384
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:29,052
You think of something.

385
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:30,788
Then I'll ask you twenty
million questions

386
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:32,957
until I can come up with
what you're thinking of.

387
00:16:33,359 --> 00:16:34,125
          Let's go!

388
00:16:34,327 --> 00:16:34,892
           Is it blue?

389
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:35,593
          Is it green?

390
00:16:35,695 --> 00:16:36,294
           Is it red?

391
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:37,095
       Is it greenish-red?

392
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:37,995
       Is it reddish-blue?

393
00:16:38,097 --> 00:16:39,395
 Is it bigger than a bread box?

394
00:16:39,497 --> 00:16:40,595
 Is it smaller than a bread box?

395
00:16:40,697 --> 00:16:41,599
       Is it a bread box?

396
00:16:41,701 --> 00:16:42,400
          Is it bread?

397
00:16:42,602 --> 00:16:43,300
          Is it teeth?

398
00:16:43,402 --> 00:16:44,969
 Is it Granny Smith's dentures?

399
00:16:45,271 --> 00:16:46,204
           Is it you?

400
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:47,371
        Is it a rooster?

401
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:48,373
      Is it a red rooster?

402
00:16:48,475 --> 00:16:50,175
Is it a red rooster eating corn?

403
00:16:50,877 --> 00:16:53,111
Uhp, used up all twenty
million questions.

404
00:16:53,413 --> 00:16:54,679
Oh, well, we're here anyway!

405
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:01,185
          Official Pony
       Balloon still here?

406
00:17:01,509 --> 00:17:02,487
[shakes head]

407
00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:06,891
   Pink Pony gone because Pink
    Pony not tough like yaks.

408
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:09,694
     Horn bump in agreement.

409
00:17:10,096 --> 00:17:10,695
              Now!

410
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:11,619
[horn bump]

411
00:17:13,632 --> 00:17:15,500
             [chomp]

412
00:17:16,268 --> 00:17:16,967
             Bleagh!

413
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:19,103
   Snow sandwich lose novelty.

414
00:17:19,305 --> 00:17:21,038
    Snow couscous for dinner.

415
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:22,173
            [grunts]

416
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:25,876
     Then Prince Rutherford
          said -- Bang!

417
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:27,545
     Pretend there is door!

418
00:17:27,647 --> 00:17:29,013
       I just slammed it!

419
00:17:29,315 --> 00:17:30,213
          Pinkie Pie--

420
00:17:30,315 --> 00:17:31,549
So then Pink
Pony said --

421
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:33,518
       Fine, be stubborn!

422
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:36,254
       Pinkie Pie, we have
        to help the yaks!

423
00:17:36,656 --> 00:17:40,091
      So in conclusion, we
     have to help the yaks!

424
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:41,059
    Hmm?

425
00:17:41,661 --> 00:17:43,027
           Just go with it, hon.

426
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:44,895
Great idea, Pinkie.

427
00:17:44,997 --> 00:17:46,597
We'll be happy to
 help the yaks.

428
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,833
This is what friendship
     is all about.

429
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:50,835
                 Hey! I'll bring
                     apples.

430
00:17:51,037 --> 00:17:53,404
             This season's batch
              are extra juicy.

431
00:17:53,706 --> 00:17:54,972
  And I shall provide the yaks

432
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:57,208
                with Equestria's
                finest textiles.

433
00:17:57,410 --> 00:18:00,077
          They'll be silky and
         warm with hints of gold

434
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:01,512
      to compliment their horns.

435
00:18:01,614 --> 00:18:02,313
                           Stop!

436
00:18:02,615 --> 00:18:05,149
       We can't bring the
      yaks any pony stuff!

437
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:06,384
                       Why not?

438
00:18:06,786 --> 00:18:08,586
The yaks are very proud.

439
00:18:08,888 --> 00:18:10,488
They won't ask for help.

440
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:13,357
You know what they say, you
can lead a yak to water,

441
00:18:13,459 --> 00:18:15,560
but you better not let
him know you're doing it!

442
00:18:15,962 --> 00:18:17,395
Nopony says that.

443
00:18:17,897 --> 00:18:18,597
    Do they?

444
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:21,399
    OK then, this will be an

445
00:18:21,501 --> 00:18:23,401
         Official Covert
       Friendship Mission.

446
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:25,102
Rainbow Dash: You got it!
Pinkie Pie: Woohoo!

447
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:26,804
      Pinkie: Is it yellow?

448
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:27,938
          Is it slimy?

449
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:29,138
       Is it slimy-yellow?

450
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:31,141
       Rainbow Dash: We're
        not playing that!

451
00:18:33,812 --> 00:18:37,181
        First, we have to
  infiltrate the yak compound!

452
00:18:38,205 --> 00:18:38,805
[clang]

453
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:41,285
      These walls are high.

454
00:18:41,487 --> 00:18:43,788
  Sneaking in will not be easy.

455
00:18:43,912 --> 00:18:46,112
               ♪♪

456
00:18:46,336 --> 00:18:48,736
[grunting]

457
00:18:48,860 --> 00:18:49,760
[door creaking]

458
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:54,365
Or it's super easy
cause I'm awesome.

459
00:18:54,667 --> 00:18:56,501
                  Go ahead. I'll
                     catch up!

460
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:58,437
                 You all know
                  what to do!

461
00:18:59,939 --> 00:19:00,538
                 [thud]

462
00:19:02,974 --> 00:19:09,944
            [snoring]

463
00:19:10,068 --> 00:19:10,616
[pop]

464
00:19:11,517 --> 00:19:46,654
               ♪♪

465
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,888
             [yawning]

466
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:51,523
               Oh!

467
00:19:52,525 --> 00:19:53,658
         What happened!?

468
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:55,559
Snow melted.

469
00:19:55,661 --> 00:19:57,295
Prince Rutherford was right!

470
00:19:57,497 --> 00:20:02,767
      [laughter and cheers]

471
00:20:03,169 --> 00:20:04,935
           Aha! Yaks tough!

472
00:20:05,237 --> 00:20:06,704
      Yaks wait patiently.

473
00:20:06,906 --> 00:20:08,372
            Yaks win!

474
00:20:09,396 --> 00:20:12,196
               ♪♪

475
00:20:12,277 --> 00:20:16,280
    Whoo-weee, helping to fix
      an entire yak village

476
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:17,949
  sure takes a lot out of you.

477
00:20:18,351 --> 00:20:19,550
Let's get out of here
before--

478
00:20:19,652 --> 00:20:21,419
       Prince: Oh Pink Pony!

479
00:20:22,021 --> 00:20:23,688
        <i> ♪ [scary music] ♪</i>

480
00:20:23,712 --> 00:20:24,489
[nervous laugh]

481
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:26,090
       Just play it cool...

482
00:20:27,058 --> 00:20:30,127
       We didn't help fix
       Yakyakistan! No no!

483
00:20:30,329 --> 00:20:31,727
 We're just here for
the snow sandwiches!

484
00:20:31,829 --> 00:20:33,998
  But.. then we got here and the
    snow's gone so we thought

485
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:36,301
   we'd hit a diner on the way
   back to Ponyville. Buh Bye!

486
00:20:36,703 --> 00:20:39,537
               Wait! Yak not mad
                 at Pink Pony.

487
00:20:39,939 --> 00:20:41,005
    Yak not?

488
00:20:41,207 --> 00:20:44,242
      Pink Pony helped yaks
      without yaks asking.

489
00:20:44,544 --> 00:20:46,844
Means Pink Pony understand yaks.

490
00:20:47,946 --> 00:20:48,779
              I do?

491
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:50,915
           Hunh! I do!

492
00:20:51,317 --> 00:20:54,385
              Pink Pony the best
                kind of friend.

493
00:20:54,787 --> 00:20:57,088
        Officially Honorary Yak!

494
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:58,556
                         Hooray!

495
00:20:58,658 --> 00:20:59,490
              Yay!

496
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:00,791
         Pink Pony Honorary Yak!

497
00:21:00,893 --> 00:21:02,260
  Yippeeee!

498
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:05,129
My own Honorary Yak Horns!

499
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:07,965
Now I can officially horn bump!

500
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:08,966
     [thunk] Oh!

501
00:21:11,368 --> 00:21:15,306
 Yeah, you know this<i> is</i> a little
  heavy for my small pony head.

502
00:21:15,408 --> 00:21:16,607
            Ha ha ha.

503
00:21:16,809 --> 00:21:18,776
       Need some help with
        that, Pinkie Pie?

504
00:21:19,078 --> 00:21:22,481
Pink Pony no need
Apple Pony's help!

505
00:21:23,283 --> 00:21:25,015
[giggle]

506
00:21:25,217 --> 00:21:26,015
Just kidding!

507
00:21:26,117 --> 00:21:27,952
Pink Pony got Apple Pony good!

508
00:21:30,055 --> 00:21:32,156
Seriously, this is
  heavy. [thud]

